caption.body: Organic life somehow emerges beneath the black waves of the first oceans in this composition and film produced as a long-distance collaboration between lifelong friends, Los Angeles-based Aurélien Rubod and London-based Michaël Stroudinsky.  See “Dans les Vagues Noires des Premiers Océans” by Rubod & Stroudinsky, now playing in the Video Arts Room located pre-security in the International Terminal. http://bit.ly/2knAYzd
